---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base
  title="About — David Gentile"
  description="David Gentile. Notes and artefacts on AI, structure, and the intelligence interface."
>
  <article class="about-wrap">
    <header class="about-head">
      <h1>About</h1>
    </header>

    <section class="about-body">
      <p>
        I'm David. I write here about the part of AI nobody is solving with a
        chat box: the layer between the model and the work, where structure,
        context, and intent actually live.
      </p>
      <p>
        My day job is building things in that space. This site is where the
        ideas get to be smaller. One claim, one artefact, no roadmap.
      </p>
      <p>
        Most posts have a small interactive built into them. The interactives
        are the argument. The prose is the caption. If a claim doesn't reward
        being felt, it stays as prose. If it does, it becomes something you
        can click through.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you like what you see, the best way to support it is to share it with someone
        else. If you want to chat about it, or are interested in  working together, find me at the links below. 
      </p>

      <h2>Where else</h2>
      <p>
        <a href="https://x.com/dfgentile" rel="me">X</a>
        <span class="dot">·</span>
        <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/davidfgentile/" rel="me">LinkedIn</a>
        <span class="dot">·</span>
        <a href="https://www.github.com/diva-D" rel="me">GitHub</a>
        <span class="dot">·</span>
        <a href="mailto:david@strategicfocus.ai">Email</a>
      </p>

      <h2>Colophon</h2>
      <p>
        Built with Astro. Hand-rolled CSS. Iowan Old Style for the body, Inter
        for the chrome. Hosted on Vercel. The artefacts are single-file vanilla
        HTML, no build step, viewable source.
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</Base>
